---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Technology" description="Deep dive into the eStream platform, post-quantum security, SmartCircuits, and AI analytics powering SynergyCarbon.">

  <header class="page-hero">
    <h1>Technology</h1>
    <p>
      Built on the eStream network with post-quantum cryptography, real-time
      verification, and AI-powered analytics.
    </p>
  </header>

  <!-- eStream Platform -->
  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title reveal">eStream Platform</h2>
    <p class="section-subtitle reveal delay-1">
      SynergyCarbon runs on the eStream v0.8.3 distributed application platform
      from PolyQuantum Labs.
    </p>

    <div class="detail-grid">
      <div class="detail-card reveal delay-1">
        <h3>SmartCircuits</h3>
        <p>
          13 SmartCircuits power the platform: PoVCR Verifier, Credit Lifecycle,
          Marketplace Matching, Forward Contract FSM, Retirement Engine,
          Governance Voting, Anomaly Detection, and more. Compiled from
          FastLang .fl to Rust/WASM via ESCIR.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="detail-card reveal delay-2">
        <h3>Real-Time Data</h3>
        <p>
          WebTransport delivers sub-second attestation verification and live
          telemetry to all connected clients. No polling, no batching, no HTTP
          fallback. DAG-based event ordering ensures consistency.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="detail-card reveal delay-3">
        <h3>Scatter-CAS Storage</h3>
        <p>
          Content-addressable storage with k-of-n erasure coding ensures data
          durability and availability. Attestation data, credit metadata, and
          audit logs are immutable and verifiable by hash.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PoVC Protocol -->
  <section class="section-surface">
    <div class="section" style="padding-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0;">
      <h2 class="section-title reveal">PoVC Protocol</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle reveal delay-1">
        Proof-of-Verified-Carbon is a four-phase attestation protocol
        linking physical energy measurements to verified carbon credits.
      </p>

      <div class="detail-grid">
        <div class="detail-card reveal delay-1">
          <h3>Attestation Format</h3>
          <p>
            Each attestation contains: node ID, GPS coordinates, timestamp, sensor
            readings (kWh, flow rate, temperature), ML-DSA-87 signature, and
            methodology reference. Batched into epoch-aligned bundles.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-card reveal delay-2">
          <h3>Quorum Verification</h3>
          <p>
            3-of-5 threshold with configurable tolerance bands per source type.
            Variance analysis flags outliers. Byzantine fault tolerance ensures
            correctness even with compromised nodes.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-card reveal delay-3">
          <h3>Credit Lifecycle States</h3>
          <p>
            Credits move through: <strong>pending</strong> &rarr;
            <strong>verified</strong> &rarr; <strong>minted</strong> &rarr;
            <strong>listed</strong> &rarr; <strong>sold</strong> &rarr;
            <strong>retired</strong>. Each transition is hash-chained and auditable.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Multi-Registry -->
  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title reveal">Multi-Registry Compatibility</h2>
    <p class="section-subtitle reveal delay-1">
      Four registry bridges prevent double-counting and enable cross-platform retirement.
    </p>

    <div class="detail-grid">
      <div class="detail-card reveal delay-1">
        <h3>Verra VCS</h3>
        <p>
          Full integration with Verra&rsquo;s Verified Carbon Standard. Serial
          number format compliance, retirement sync, and project-level reporting.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="detail-card reveal delay-2">
        <h3>Gold Standard</h3>
        <p>
          Gold Standard for the Global Goals with SDG co-benefit tracking.
          Automatic retirement notification and public registry updates.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="detail-card reveal delay-3">
        <h3>CDM</h3>
        <p>
          Clean Development Mechanism bridge for UNFCCC-registered projects.
          CER issuance tracking and cross-registry deduplication.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="detail-card reveal delay-4">
        <h3>ISCC</h3>
        <p>
          International Sustainability and Carbon Certification for biomass
          and bioenergy supply chain traceability and compliance.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- AI Analytics -->
  <section class="section-dark">
    <div style="max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 class="section-title reveal">AI Analytics</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle reveal delay-1">
        Machine learning powers yield forecasting, anomaly detection,
        and forward pricing across the platform.
      </p>

      <div class="advantages-grid">
        <div class="advantage-card reveal delay-1">
          <h3>Mamba/S4 Yield Forecasting</h3>
          <p>
            State-space sequence models predict energy yield across 7, 30, 90,
            and 365-day horizons. Per-source confidence intervals with RLHF
            operator feedback corrections.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="advantage-card reveal delay-2">
          <h3>Forward Pricing Oracle</h3>
          <p>
            Supply elasticity modeling, seasonal patterns, and market sentiment
            analysis produce fair-value estimates for forward contracts with
            uncertainty quantification.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="advantage-card reveal delay-3">
          <h3>Anomaly Detection</h3>
          <p>
            Real-time monitoring flags sensor drift, calibration issues, and
            suspicious attestation patterns. Automatic quorum challenge triggers
            when anomaly scores exceed thresholds.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Security -->
  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title reveal">Post-Quantum Security</h2>
    <p class="section-subtitle reveal delay-1">
      Every layer of the platform is protected by NIST-approved
      post-quantum cryptographic primitives.
    </p>

    <div class="detail-grid">
      <div class="detail-card reveal delay-1">
        <h3>ML-DSA-87 (Dilithium)</h3>
        <p>
          NIST FIPS 204 digital signatures for attestations, credit minting,
          retirement proofs, and all governance actions. 4,627-byte signatures
          with 128-bit post-quantum security level.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="detail-card reveal delay-2">
        <h3>ML-KEM-1024 (Kyber)</h3>
        <p>
          NIST FIPS 203 key encapsulation for encrypted communication between
          witness nodes, verifiers, and the console. Forward secrecy with
          ephemeral key exchange.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="detail-card reveal delay-3">
        <h3>SPARK Authentication</h3>
        <p>
          Visual challenge-response authentication eliminates password-based
          attacks. Biometric binding with device attestation. Anti-phishing
          by design &mdash; no credentials to steal.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Console Kit -->
  <section class="section-surface">
    <div class="section" style="padding-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0;">
      <h2 class="section-title reveal">Console Kit</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle reveal delay-1">
        14 real-time widgets, RBAC access control, and a full demo mode
        for evaluation and training.
      </p>

      <div class="detail-grid">
        <div class="detail-card reveal delay-1">
          <h3>14 Widgets</h3>
          <p>
            Dashboard overview, attestation feed, credit registry, marketplace
            orderbook, forward contracts, impact dashboard, retirement manager,
            yield forecast, anomaly alerts, governance panel, audit log,
            node status, analytics, and settings.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-card reveal delay-2">
          <h3>RBAC Access Control</h3>
          <p>
            Role-based access with 4 tiers: admin, operator, auditor, and viewer.
            Fine-grained permissions per widget and data scope. Integrates with
            SPARK identity and ML-DSA-87 session tokens.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-card reveal delay-3">
          <h3>Demo Mode</h3>
          <p>
            Full-featured demo with simulated attestation data, synthetic credits,
            and mock marketplace activity. No signup required &mdash; explore every
            widget before committing.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section" style="text-align: center;">
    <h2 class="section-title reveal">See It in Action</h2>
    <p class="section-subtitle reveal delay-1">
      Explore the full platform with our interactive demo console.
    </p>
    <div class="reveal delay-2">
      <a href="https://console.synergycarbon.io?demo=true" class="btn-primary" style="margin-right: 0.75rem;">Try Demo Console</a>
      <a href="/api" class="btn-outline" style="color: var(--sc-primary-dark); border-color: var(--sc-primary-dark);">API Reference</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
